    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nHaving a robust logging mechanism in Neovim core would allow plugins to easily log to a singular location that users know to look for, making it easier users to provide more useful context for plugin authors.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNot entirely sure the best approach, but I think something similar in spirit to VSCode's [Output Panel](https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/getstarted/userinterface#_basic-layout) would be nice.\r\n\r\nKey benefits would be having logging channels per LSP client and plugins (in VSCode, an extensions can make arbitrary \"output channels\" and name them whatever they'd like).\r\n\r\nThey are easy to view and locate in the UI.\r\n\r\nI have a plugin that mimics this behavior for LSP clients, but can't currently be used for arbitrary output. https://github.com/mhanberg/output-panel.nvim\r\n\r\nThese logs are not persisted, but just live in memory.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure what a core nvim UI for this would look like (tab per channel?, floating window with tab in in the winbar?) or if it would just provide a core api, and a plugin can provide a nicer UI for it.\r\n\r\nThanks for the consideration!",
